      "contentFieldValue": {
        "data": "<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">\n  <strong>Note:</strong> please note that Liferay has renamed its Liferay Experience\n  Could offerings to <i><strong>Liferay SaaS</strong></i> (formerly LXC) and\n  <i><strong>Liferay PaaS</strong></i> (formerly LXC-SM).\n</div>\n<p class=\"article-title\" title=\"API Update Release Announcement\"><strong>Published: June 27, 2022</strong></p>\n<div class=\"article-content\">\n<section class=\"article-body\">\n<h2 id=\"h_01HYXHHFFZG7HY46KYVQJ6RQ0G\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Summary</span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In order to keep your Cloud environment up-to-date and your running services authenticated and error free, Liferay Cloud has deployed an updated Elasticsearch license for all Liferay PaaS customers. With this change, we want to address any behavior you may see and steps to perform in order to leverage this update.<br></span></p>\n<h2 id=\"h_01HYXHHFFZ71383F712T1XF5KM\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Details</span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You may have noticed the following error in your search service:</span></p>\n<pre><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\"License [will expire] on [Wednesday, June 29, 2022].\\n# If you have a new license, please update it. Otherwise, please reach out to\\n# your support contact</span></pre>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Please do not be alarmed, your search service will continue to run as expected.</span></p>\n<h2 id=\"h_01HYXHHFFZ2S8QG8HRVBFDYPYF\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Resolution</span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In order to leverage the new license, you will need to perform one of the following steps:<br></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Restart your search service</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OR</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Redeploy your search service</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Restarting or Redeploying will allow the search service to recognize and utilize the new license. You will continue to see the error mentioned above until you perform one of these steps.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"wysiwyg-underline\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Please note that, if you do not have a volume set up for your search service, you may need to reindex your search indices after performing a restart or redeploy. See our <a href=\"https://help.liferay.com/hc/en-us/articles/7239716043917\" target=\"_self\">Missing Search Indices After Restart/Redeploy</a> for more information.</span></span></p>\n<h2 id=\"h_01HYXHHFG0GSFNS40552R7PBZM\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Additional Information</span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As always, if you encounter any issues or have questions about these changes, please </span><a href=\"https://help.liferay.com/hc/requests/new\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"undefined\">submit a ticket</a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and Liferay Support will be happy to assist.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span></p>\n</section>\n</div>"
      },
